The white keys on a piano correspond to the notes of the **chromatic scale**, which include both fundamental degrees (e.g., C in C major) and non-fundamental notes (e.g., C#/Db). While they *can* form major/minor scales, they are not *always* fundamental degrees (e.g., enharmonic equivalents like C# and Db). Option C is misleading because it implies exclusivity, which isn’t true.
